      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your logic is flawed because the body does not \"flush out\" excess Vitamin D quickly; it stores the fat-soluble vitamin in your adipose tissue, meaning a 14-day overload can accumulate into dangerous toxicity levels over time. Even if you feel healthy, a 50,000 IU daily dose for two weeks is a massive spike that can induce acute hypercalcemia, leading to severe kidney damage and cardiac arrhythmias. The only safe way to maximize your immune system is to get a blood test first, then follow a prescribed protocol rather than guessing based on blog advice.",
